{{Infobox language |name=Putai |states=[[Nigeria]] |region=[[Borno State]] |speakers=50 |date=no date |ref=e15<!--same figure in e17--> |familycolor=Afro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Chadic languages|Chadic]] |fam3=[[Biu–Mandara languages|Biu–Mandara]] |fam4=Bura–Higi |fam5=[[Bura languages|Bura]] (A.2) |iso3=mfl |glotto=puta1243 |glottorefname=Putai |lingua=18-GBB-c }}
'''Putai''' (also known as Marghi West) is a nearly extinct [[Afro-Asiatic languages|Afro-Asiatic]] language spoken in [[Nigeria]]. The language is dying out and being replaced by [[Kanuri language|Kanuri]].<ref name=e15/>
